reminded myself that it is okay to live & take a “break” even if it’s only for a few hours…went to the beach to catch the sunrise(which is one of my favorite things, yet i haven’t done it in years)

since i started @theproductivemanic back in june 2022 i have let it consume me and i don’t regret it. but with that being said a lot of sacrifices have been made in order to continue to grow the shop whether it be spending 95% of the money i make from the shop back into the shop, relationships love & friends & family and majority of the time not being able to go out and have fun or having to cancel last minute because of being overworked or lack of sleep.

but with sacrifices and hard work comes a lot of amazing things too. i am the most independent i’ve been in my entire life, can finally pay my bills, no longer scares me to spend so much time alone nor feeling like i am missing out on fun
(i spent most of my life not being able to function unless i had someone by my side, or having fun and worrying about everyone else and not giving two shits about my future so it’s becoming easier day by day to realize i need to focus on myself mentally & physically) and most importantly i feel the most authentic, healthy physically & spirituality in my whole life rn.

i used to play the blame game majority of my life as to why i’ve been stuck most of my life and repeating the same damn cycles thinking something would change or an opportunity would arise out of a blue. people and things have stopped me from A LOT but what has stopped me the most from being successful & pure happiness is MYSELF and not being CONSISTENT & not KNOWING MY WORTH.

but the point of this rant is to remind myself and others to focus on yourself & your mental health & being a better person, keep working, keep creating, & keep finding time to do what you love and remember the point of life isn’t to be working 24/7 nor trying to be a people pleaser when you’re not even happy yourself.

~now back to me posting aesthetically pleasing pics & making people forget that there is a human being behind the screen who is working their ass off & hoping it pays off~

23 things i learned/reminded of in 2023 thus far✨

1. TRUST YOUR INTUITION
2. LOVE YOURSELF
3. FOCUS ON YOURSELF & YOUR HAPPINESS
4.  if your friends/family don’t support you & your business publicly/behind closed doors they aren’t that great of friends & family after all.
5. hurt people hurt people but that doesn’t excuse their actions. 
6. the more work you put into yourself, the more abundance you’ll receive.
7. if someone says they’re not good enough for you and that you deserve better, BELIEVE THEM & run
8. everything people say to and about you is a projection and says more about them than you.
9. if you don’t trust someone don’t surround yourself with them, let alone be friends or date them. 
10. the truth ALWAYS comes to light one way or another so you might as well tell the truth.
11. most things aren’t nor shouldn’t be a competition, theres enough room for everyone to succeed & prosper. 
12. you are who you surround yourself with so if someone is surrounded by shitty/untrustworthy people, they can’t be trusted either.
13. it’s always the ones your significant other says “are just friends” or you shouldn’t worry about that you really should worry about.
14. beautiful, amazing, good people get cheated on daily, has nothing to do with you, the person you are with is just weak.
15. if you can’t do anything without be high or drunk or need it in order to have fun then clearly it’s a problem. 
16. money isn’t evil, money doesn’t make people evil, money just brings out whatever that person is whether its good or evil.
17. 9/10 its best to let people talk & gossip about you even if its lies, but sometimes enough is enough and it’s okay to speak up & speak the truth, the truth will set you free.
18. the law of attraction & karma are working 24/7 whether you believe it or not.
19. listen more, people tell on themselves & their motives.
20. eating good, getting sleep, feeding your mind and soul can change your life.
21. mental health is just as important as physical health, and sometimes even more important.
22. give back as much as possible whether it is your time, energy, money.
23. 2023 is going to be the year of growth, happiness, truth, judgment & abundance.

last day of winter, all black outfit was a must.

happy first day of spring!!!!
i am so stoked for whats to come when it comes to work, projects, growth, travel, love and everything in between🍃🌼🌷🌞

and for those who suffer from seasonal depression like i do, we made it through another winter!!!
i was diagnosed with seasonal depression 7 years ago which finally gave me some knowledge & reassurance as to why every winter i’ve always had rather rough winters whether it being super depressed, exhausted, moody, irritated, and not wanting to leave the house & so on.

i am happy to say this past winter has been the best yet!! still a battle and a lot of bad things and toxic ways did happen from time to time but the good & growth outweighed the negative and honestly i was too busy and overworked to feel much😅

felt the need to share this lil insight because you truly never know what someones going through and dealing with depression and many other things have made me a rather good actor ;) & well aware a smile can hide a lot. 
also wanted to share because i know a lot of people either don’t know about seasonal depression or think it’s fake…. or think you can only get it if you live somewhere that has a harsh winter…

i do plan to talk more in detail about this and other mental health things in the near future when i am more comfortable speaking on camera but till then swipe for a short video clip & i uploaded the other 30 seconds of the video on my story!

i hope spring is good to us all✨🖤
#happyhomeygood

happy 420!!!
i am so proud of myself and happy to announce i’ve been sober from weed for a year in a half!!!!!
which is I N S A N E 
fun fact, i’ve been a highly functioning stoner boy for 10 years of my life…. and majority of those 10 years i would be high from the time i woke up to the time i went to bed.
and if i wasn’t high i would be either annoyed, bored, angry, have major anxiety etc.

i quit smoking when i first moved to jacksonville florida last year january 2022, wasn’t my intention at all.. it was just really hard to get quality stuff being in a new city and finally after the amount of time and effort i was putting into trying to get it i realized i had a damn problem(which i already knew) so i just stopped and managed to actually stick with it for once in my life whether it be because i for once was not around people who smoke, i stayed busy, i treated it as a challenge & really wanted to test myself and see if i was for once capable of stopping completely plus i was rather intrigued by the thought of wondering what my mind and my energy would be like if i stopped fully, cuz i truly couldn’t even remember what i was like before i smoked…
and the rest is history✨

you don’t know how proud of myself i am for so many reasons and i am not even going to lie i smoked less than 10 times in january of this year & needless to say it wasn’t satisfying, rather waste of time, wasn’t like it used to be & if i wasn’t trying to relate to someone i liked in january (needless to say that person is irrelevant to my life now LOL) i would have remained sober but hey i still consider myself being sober from weed for a year in a half even tho i smoked a lil this year and i plan to remain free from weed, i also just decided recently to no longer drink either or do any drug, so wish me luck
✨💃🏽👏🏽🧿
